    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like your Monstera deliciosa might be experiencing a few issues, possibly due to overwatering or a fungal infection. Yellowing leaves and brown spots can be a sign of waterlogged soil. Try reducing the watering frequency to once every 7-10 days and ensure the pot has good drainage. A little bit of sunlight can help, so consider moving it to a spot where it gets more direct light. If the problem persists, you might want to check for a fungal infection, which can be treated with a fungicide. Keep an eye out for any signs of insect activity too, as they can sometimes cause similar symptoms.",
